# GameNative — Game Settings Sheet Redesign + Version Picker

## Overview — what this fixes and adds

**Chip problems (fixed).** The root issue was that chips had no fixed height and used `fillMaxWidth()` individually instead of sharing width equally. The new **EqualWidthChipRow** gives every chip **`weight(1f)`** so they all get exactly the same width, and **`height(44.dp)`** is hardcoded so no chip can ever be taller than another. **"Uncapped"** is shown as **"Off"** so it fits in one line — if product requires the full word, use **`widthIn(min = 64.dp)`** as a fallback in the constraints section.

**Version picker in the sheet.** The version picker is built into the sheet directly. There is a new **"Compatibility Layer"** navigation row at the bottom of the Runtime section. Tapping it opens a **second bottom sheet** layered on top of the settings sheet. That inner sheet shows all versions from the **merged manifest** — grouped by source (Proton-GE, Wine, Proton Valve, Wine-GE), with **LATEST** and **RECOMMENDED** badges, installed status, and **Download** buttons for anything not yet installed. The download uses **`launchManifestContentInstall`** — the same install flow already used for every other component — so no new download code is needed.

**Visual hierarchy.** Section headers (Performance, Graphics, Runtime) in small uppercase tertiary text give the sheet structure. Field labels sit directly above their chip rows. The **Save** button uses **`weight(2f)`** so it is visually twice as wide as Cancel, making the primary action obvious. The overall sheet uses **`gnBgDeepest`** background matching the rest of the app instead of a lighter surface.

---

## What's wrong with the current sheet (reference screenshot)

1. Frame cap chips are vertical — "Uncapped" is taller than the others because
   the text wraps vertically. All chips must be the same height, horizontal text.
2. Resolution scale chips have inconsistent sizing — 100% is much wider than 50%.
   All chips must be equal width.
3. No Proton/Wine version picker — users can't choose which version to use
   for this game from the settings sheet. This is the most requested missing feature.
4. No visual hierarchy — everything is the same weight with no grouping.
5. Cancel/Save buttons at the bottom are fine but Save should be more prominent.

